---
// The "Signing in" panel: how editors authenticate at /admin/editor/. The wired
// live path is Password (backed by cms-auth-worker/); Local always works from a
// dev server; GitHub OAuth is an opt-in alternative that needs its own relay.
// Static content — the authoritative setup steps live in CMS_SETUP.md.
---

<section
  style="margin-top: var(--space-xl); background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: var(--space-lg);"
>
  <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);">Signing in</h2>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-md); color: var(--color-muted); max-width: var(--text-width);">
    This dashboard is a read-only summary — actual editing happens in the editor
    once you sign in. On the live site the wired path is <strong>Password</strong>;
    <strong>Local</strong> works whenever you run a dev server. See
    <code>CMS_SETUP.md</code> for the full setup of each.
  </p>
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 2;">
    <li>
      <strong>Password</strong> (live) — the editor shows a password prompt backed by the
      Cloudflare Worker in <code>cms-auth-worker/</code>, which commits with its stored token.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Local</strong> — open this site from a local dev server and choose “Work with
      Local Repository.” No account, no server.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>GitHub OAuth</strong> — an alternative for per-user commit attribution; not wired
      by default (needs its own OAuth relay; see <code>CMS_SETUP.md</code>).
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
